t and plan every moment but you can not cheat the weather.\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1065, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the weather\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than an inch of rain fell during the ceremony, the equivalent of 15 days of rainfall in just four sopping hours.\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1183, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"More than an inch\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1083}, {\"ngram\": \"rain\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1091}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1116}, {\"ngram\": \"the equivalent\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1132}, {\"ngram\": \"15 days\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"rainfall\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1155}, {\"ngram\": \"just four sopping hours\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1182}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was certainly no perfect summer's sunset over the city's postcard landmarks.Il pleut des cordes, as we might say.\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no perfect summer's sunset\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1231}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's postcard landmarks\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1266}, {\"ngram\": \"pleut\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1275}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All of the city's iconic sites were used, the Mona Lisa was stolen (and returned) and the crowd in the Trocadero, some of whom had paid over \\u00a32,500 for their tickets, did their best to stay engaged, even if they were watching virtually all the ceremony unfold on a big screen that kept shorting out.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1605, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the city's iconic sites\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1336}, {\"ngram\": \"the Mona Lisa\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1361}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"the Trocadero\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1418}, {\"ngram\": \"their tickets\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1471}, {\"ngram\": \"virtually all the ceremony\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1558}, {\"ngram\": \"a big screen\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over 300,000 braved the weather and the stringent security checks to line the river, cheering athletes from 205 nations and the Olympic refugee team as they travelled by boat from the Place de la Bastille past a cathedral rising from the ashes under the majestic Pont Alexandre to the Trocadero, shivering under the shadow of Gustave Eiffel's iconic tower.\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1791, \"end\": 1811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Bastille\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Place de la Bastille\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Bastille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Bastille\"}, {\"begin\": 1933, \"end\": 1947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gustave Eiffel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the weather\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1638}, {\"ngram\": \"the stringent security checks\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1672}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1690}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1709}, {\"ngram\": \"205 nations\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1726}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic refugee team\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1755}, {\"ngram\": \"boat\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"a cathedral\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1828}, {\"ngram\": \"the ashes\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1850}, {\"ngram\": \"the majestic Pont Alexandre\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1884}, {\"ngram\": \"the Trocadero\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1901}, {\"ngram\": \"the shadow\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1929}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Daley and Helen Glover were very British about it, waving their flag while looking like they had just taken a plunge off the 10m highborn in their clothes.\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 2124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1965, \"end\": 1974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.005521118774043e-36, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}, {\"begin\": 1979, \"end\": 1991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553500259, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808579173, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their flag\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2037}, {\"ngram\": \"a plunge\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2085}, {\"ngram\": \"the 10m highborn\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2106}, {\"ngram\": \"their clothes\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were pictured at the bow of their boat recreating that famous scene from the Titanic, which you have to hope is not a metaphor for the high hopes Team GB arrive at these Games with.\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2277, \"end\": 2284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9593980668922744, \"rank\": 0.042259539407305494, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bow\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2155}, {\"ngram\": \"their boat\", \"from\": 2159, \"to\": 2169}, {\"ngram\": \"that famous scene\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2198}, {\"ngram\": \"the Titanic\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2215}, {\"ngram\": \"a metaphor\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2257}, {\"ngram\": \"the high hopes\", \"from\"